channel.title: 3 Frustrating Problems! Want a challange?
channel.description:
I worked hard on this to make it easier for you guys. AKA: added pics XD
Okay, so I have three problems.
[s]1. My compiler On this source, my compiler doesn't work. I will be showing you what is in the compiler and where my client.java is at. [/s]
2. My server will not appear online. It worked fine for 2 weeks and now it's all messed up. No matter what source I run.
3. My client. Where do I put the IP? It is Bluurr's Client but there is no Gui.java?
[s]So! #1! Here is what is in my compiler (btw I have the latest version of JDK)[/s] [IMG]http://i883.photobucket.com/albums/ac38/Summer_Snow1200/CompileEdit.jpg[/img] [s]That's what is in my compiler. So if I have to put something else in there, tell me. Here is how you get to my client.java that I want to compile:[/s] [IMG]http://i883.photobucket.com/albums/ac38/Summer_Snow1200/Step1.jpg[/img] [IMG]http://i883.photobucket.com/albums/ac38/Summer_Snow1200/Step2.jpg[/img] [IMG]http://i883.photobucket.com/albums/ac38/Summer_Snow1200/Step3.jpg[/img]
#2! My server(s) were working fine. No problems whatsoever. But then it basically crashed on me. Nothing worked. Nothing changed either (that I am aware of). I did use my router's IP (10.0.0.2) but that no longer works for any source. I am now using no-ip (tormentedmemories.no-ip.info). Here is my client.java of my IP: [IMG]http://i883.photobucket.com/albums/ac38/Summer_Snow1200/Step4.jpg[/img] [IMG]http://i883.photobucket.com/albums/ac38/Summer_Snow1200/Step5.jpg[/img]
Finally, #3! Here is my client folder (entire thing from top to bottom) [IMG]http://i883.photobucket.com/albums/ac38/Summer_Snow1200/Step7.jpg[/img] [IMG]http://i883.photobucket.com/albums/ac38/Summer_Snow1200/Step8.jpg[/img] [IMG]http://i883.photobucket.com/albums/ac38/Summer_Snow1200/Step9.jpg[/img]
There's only a Gui.class? :confused: I have: Teamviewer AIM Skype Ventrilo

item.title: 3 Frustrating Problems! Want a challange?
item.dc:creator: @WaleedScape WaleedScape
item.description:
@WaleedScape wrote:

OK, so, u will have to edit your compiler to YOUR version of JDK
ok, so lets say ur version was JDK 13
Right click the compiler and click “edit”
then, change the version of JDK, to urs,
for example: jdk1.6.0_18\Bin\javac.exe
change the 18 to your latest version of JDK,
hope i helped!
oh, and if u need a compiler, heres on for ya!

@echo off
title Compile
cd Source
“C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_18\Bin\javac.exe” -cp . -d ./Bin/ ./*java
pause

DDDUUUUUDDDDEEEE
in the source file, the IP is supposed to stay 127.0.0.1!!
you do not change the IP in the source, only the client.
This happened to me b4, my server wasnt online, therefore, i realised that the ip in the source file, 127.0.0.1 has to stay!
btw, in Bluurrs client, you can change the IP from Client.java

item.title: 3 Frustrating Problems! Want a challange?
item.dc:creator: @gunz4life gunz4life
item.description:
@gunz4life wrote:

1st problem, open up your compiler (notepad), and remove everything and place this in it.

@echo off
title Compiler
javac *.java
pause

2nd error:

Open your CMD type “ipconfig”, maybe your IP changed, it happens to me, if so, then go to your router page, and update it with your current IP.

3rd error:

I see the GUI.class, looks as if the owner removed the .java tho. You may be able do it with client.java, or re-extract the client, you might of deleted it accidentally.

Read full topic

item.title: 3 Frustrating Problems! Want a challange?
item.dc:creator: @Schilling Schilling
item.description:
@Schilling wrote:

For your second problem make sure you have the ports 43594 open correctly.

For your third problem, you could open Gui.class and look for the IP that it currently has, then use Z-FileSearcher to search for that IP… If it doesn’t find any .Java files with the IP then make a backup of your Gui.class and try to edit the IP there (this will probably cause an error, but I don’t know, so keep a backup of Gui.class). You should try posting this in client help…

Read full topic
